http server which requires only ~200 KB stack memory, and one chunk of heap memory (maybe 1KB) for the command line options parser.

throughput is ~75MB/s
max clients 1024
uses only one thread
cpu usage is 0.0 when idle and around 10% on full throttle on a 2 ghz machine.

recommended to use with musl libc, statically linked

needs libulz https://github.com/rofl0r/libulz
and rocksock https://github.com/rofl0r/rocksock

allows to run scripts, check the included perl-interface.

it is recommended to pass a directory with tempfs as working directory to the executable.


